to be honest i m severely disappointed this is not just a matter of inspiration i can t make a game based on a tunisian plumber saving a princess and be like yo i m just inspired by mario and this is my original game just in the same way i can t just take the death note the whole concept of the anime take it exactly as it is make a movie with it and claim it to be my original movie this is what is frustrating me from you horcujet as you don t want to label it as a fan made movie as it normally should be called and you justified the use of the death note note book as a detail when the whole movie depends on it ya3ni ma3atech detail hedha everything relies on it 7ata mel events i expected a more unique touch but turns out they re all severely inspired and similar to those of the original anime the movie itself is not satisfying and was surprisingly short and did not take the time to elaborate on many points and insist on the meaning behind the movie especially towards the end the interactive choices as well while many of them were decent and gave a pretty cool vibe others were surprisingly frustrating making me go back in the movie and hence concluding that my choice was pretty much fruitless since it just made me go back or changed something trivial and not so important technically omour montage w shooting w video quality it s professional but if the whole idea the most important part of a movie is ill founded then that would be a let down surtout menek horcujet ba3d l experience mte3a sadeem and all the creativity talk why re interpret an existing and renowned concept when you can come up with your own idea and your own concept and style from scratch i d really love to see your fully original plots and concepts and i think you should aim for an artistic independance because you are absolutely capable of it your intro remake mte3a netflix the intro of the movie is that of black mirror without forgetting the whole soundtrack is death note s ost i know it s probably just a joke but i believe it s just a bit way too much i know that this has taken lots of efforts and i totally understand how tough that may feel as a creator myself but that doesn t prevent me from criticising what i see unfit for the hope of better tunisian productions in the future that s the meaning of it all we respectfully analyse and discuss for a brighter future donc ya3tikom essa7a regardless i m still disappointed and frustrated by the movie but i ll always keep looking forward for your next projects and endeavors hopefully after taking the criticism you receive
